The paper discusses the optimization of beamwidth and alignment delay in millimeter wave small cell networks with relay nodes, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses interference management and resource allocation, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of millimeter wave technology is a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also uses a meta-heuristic optimization approach, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of scheduling strategies on system performance, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
